 / 2;background-image:url(data:image/jpeg;base64,)" class="x100 opc bgpc ofcv bgscv block to03 y100 o100 bgrn abs pen fill noscript:o0"></div></div></a></div></article><div class="b-gray400 bb pen my16"></div></div><div class="f fdc jcb"><article class="grid col1-min"><div class="grid sy8 mb8 mr8 col1 row1"><h2 class="c-black ff-fontC fw-fontC fs-fontC lh13 fs16 sm:fs18"><a class="tdn hover:o70 td300" data-link="spa" href="/healthy-living/article/ideal-diet-4-year-old-kids-18013690.php">The Ideal Diet for 4 Year Old Kids</a></h2></div><div class="grid sy8 col1span2 row2"></div><div class="block col2 row1 ml8 x78px xs:x100px sm:x140px lg:x78px x90px sm:x112px"><a data-link="spa" href="/healthy-living/article/ideal-diet-4-year-old-kids-18013690.php"><div class="rel x100 block"><img title="The Ideal Diet for 4 Year Old Kids" alt="healhty vegan lunch bowl with ingredients. Avocado, quinoa, sweet potato, tomato, spinach and chickpeas vegetables salad. Top view" loading="lazy" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_80.webp 80w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_160.webp 160w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_240.webp 240w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_360.webp 360w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_480.webp 480w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_640.webp 640w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_720.webp 720w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_960.webp 960w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_1080.webp 1080w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_1440.webp 1440w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/32/44/06/23740808/3/ratio3x2_1920.webp 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 240px, (max-width: 480px) 360px, 480px" style="aspect-ratio:3 / 2" class="x100 opc bgpc ofcv bgscv block to03 y100 o0 noscript:o100 mnh0"/><div style="aspect-ratio:3 / 2;background-image:url(data:image/jpeg;base64,)" class="x100 opc bgpc ofcv bgscv block to03 y100 o100 bgrn abs pen fill noscript:o0"></div></div></a></div></article></div></div></div></div><div class="pt16 mb32 sy16 bb bt b-gray300"><div><p class="ff-fontE fw-fontE fs-fontE lh12 fs12 f aic jcc ttu">Advertisement</p><p class="ff-fontG fw-fontG fs-fontG lh12 fs12 f aic jcc">Article continues below this ad</p></div><div class="tac mb16 sm:mnh300px mnh300px" data-block-type="ad" data-small-id="Inline-1" data-large-id="Inline-2" data-unit="hnp-weekand.com/article_dtc"></div></div><div class="re6bgoq d1uy5mhj ff-fontJ fw-fontJ fs-fontJ lh18 ps32 fs18"><h2>Nutrition</h2></div><div class="re6bgoq d1uy5mhj ff-fontJ fw-fontJ fs-fontJ lh18 ps32 fs18"><p>Restaurant and other commercially prepared foods are notoriously high in fat, salt and sugar. These foods are fine as an occasional indulgence or for a special occasion, but not healthy as a regular diet. Preparing most of your meals at home helps train your palate toward healthier fare. Your creative cooking skills are bound to improve considerably as you learn enjoyable ways to cook with flavorful and healthy ingredients. More meals cooked and eaten at home may help trim the national waistline and turn the tide on the obesity epidemic.</p></div><div class="re6bgoq d1uy5mhj ff-fontJ fw-fontJ fs-fontJ lh18 ps32 fs18"><h2>Food Safety</h2></div><div class="re6bgoq d1uy5mhj ff-fontJ fw-fontJ fs-fontJ lh18 ps32 fs18"><p>Food-borne illnesses caused by bacteria-laden or under-cooked meats and vegetables regularly make headlines and occasionally claim lives. According to University of Kansas food safety expert Dr. Douglas Powell, up to 25 percent of the population succumbs to a food-borne illness each year to a total cost of $1.4 trillion. While food you buy at the grocery store might be similarly contaminated, attention to proper food handling and cooking techniques may keep you safer.</p></div><div class="pt16 mb32 sy16 bb bt b-gray300"><div><p class="ff-fontE fw-fontE fs-fontE lh12 fs12 f aic jcc ttu">Advertisement</p><p class="ff-fontG fw-fontG fs-fontG lh12 fs12 f aic jcc">Article continues below this ad</p></div><div class="tac mb16 sm:mnh300px mnh300px" data-block-type="ad" data-small-id="Inline-2" data-large-id="Inline-3" data-unit="hnp-weekand.com/article_dtc"></div></div><div class="re6bgoq d1uy5mhj ff-fontJ fw-fontJ fs-fontJ lh18 ps32 fs18"><h2>Family Dynamics</h2></div><div class="re6bgoq d1uy5mhj ff-fontJ fw-fontJ fs-fontJ lh18 ps32 fs18"><p>Children benefit greatly from the ritual of eating meals together. Family meals provide opportunities for sharing the day&#x27;s events and create a relaxing transition from busy daytime activities to slower-paced evening ones. Cooking meals at home and involving your children in food preparation is the best way to teach them healthy eating habits. Statistically, children who grow up in households where meals are eaten together perform better academically and show less tendency toward engaging in risky behaviors such as smoking, drinking and taking drugs, according to Washington State University nutrition researchers Martha Marina and Sue Butkus.</p></div><div class="y1px x100 abs bgn top"></div><div style="top:25%" class="y1px x100 abs bgn"></div><div style="top:50%" class="y1px x100 abs bgn"></div><div style="top:75%" class="y1px x100 abs bgn"></div><div class="y1px x100 abs bgn bottom"></div></article></div><div class="package"><span class="mb16 block"><span class="ff-fontG fw-fontG fs-fontG lh12 ps1 lg:fs16 fs14 c-gray600"><time dateTime="2012-05-22 08:00:00">May 22, 2012</time></span><span class="ff-fontG fw-fontG fs-fontG lh12 ps1 lg:fs16 fs14 c-gray600"><span class="px8">|</span>Updated<!-- --> <time dateTime="2018-12-14 01:38:43">December 14, 2018 1:38 a.m.</time></span></span><div class="bt bb b-gray400 py16 pr8"><div class="f aic jcb fw g8"><div class="f fdc sy4"><span class="c-gray700 f aic g2 fw"><span class="ff-fontD fw-fontD 